text:
Morningside Park: A series of three views forming a panoramic arrangement as photographed from the 110th Street station of the 9th Avenue "El". Morningside Drive separates the park from the Protestant Episcopal Cathedral of St. John and forms the westerly boundary. Manhattan Avenue at the right performs a similar function.
June 6, 1940
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
title: Manhattan: Morningside Park.
